Bot-development, scripting  / programming isn't a game.
<br />
Just like you say you've frozen your account, but you still are on #anarchyonline every day, and you still do your coding / DB / character-statistics and alot of AO-related activities because of your scripting/DB/coding/programming-interest to keep auno.org running to continue to provide that service, even when you're sick of the game itself. This is the exact same thing.
<br />

<br />
I "left AO" long before I got banned. I left it, and froze my account for real even before I got banned, then CZ(FC) convinced me and tricked me into coming back ingame, just to get banned 1 1/2 years ago.
<br />
I left and announced why I left, then they invited and convinced me back in, just to be able to ban me "officially" to save face after I had left and announced publically that I left because of Funcom's Ill management.
<br />

<br />
I havent played AO for 2 1/2 years, I've just logged in now and then when there are ingame graphical issues with bot that needs fixing when Funcom has patched with chat-socket changes etc.
<br />

<br />
Just because it's their game, doesn't mean they have the rights to continously contact X-customers outside their own servers for any given reason, atleast that's "weird" behavior. And for the account, they very much discussed that too in public earlier, and allready violated their own EULA before, but that's another issue this post wasnt really about.
<br />

<br />
I'm only stating what i think is ethically right / wrong, and why I'm not willing to bother with IGN anymore because of that, and has nothing to do with me enjoying playing AO or not, since i've stopped playing AO over 2 1/2 years ago by choice, long before I got banned.
<br />

<br />
It's only some of the people in AO, and working with bot's that has kept me here, nothing else, not AO. I'm not leaving AO, left that long ago in playing-terms. I'm leaving IGN. Hopefully for good this time.
<br />

<br />
I didn't make this thread to discuss all the sub-issues of AO-playing or not, or the rights or not of Funcom, but simply what I think is too ethically wrong to continue with anything that is related to Funcom, thus working with ao-bots.
<br />
I posted also cause I believe Funcom don't care much about fixing serious issues unless they're shown it undeniably right in their faces.
<br />
And I believe the customers deserve to know what kind of people they trust their security with, their accounts, VISA-information / billing information etc.
<br />
If they care so little that they don't fix something like that serious crashpacket that they've been warned about for years, then I'd strongly think twice about their security priorities on other more severe things, like account-information, billing-information and that they might be slow to fix issues like that aswell if they were to go wrong some time.
<br />

<br />
I also posted because where I come from/live, it's the polite thing to do, to notice why you are leaving something ex. a project, instead of just leaving.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
